@startuml Sequence_Complete_System_Overview

actor Customer
actor Admin
actor Staff
actor Tailor
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
participant "Payment Gateway" as Payment

== Complete System Workflow ==

== 1. Customer Registration & Login ==
Customer -> Frontend: Register/Login
Frontend -> API: Auth endpoints
API -> DB: User management
DB --> API: User data
API --> Frontend: Auth token
Frontend --> Customer: Dashboard access

== 2. Customer Places Order ==
Customer -> Frontend: Browse & Select Fabric
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics
API -> DB: Fetch fabrics
DB --> API: Fabric data

Customer -> Frontend: Place Order
Frontend -> API: POST /api/orders
API -> DB: Create order\nUpdate fabric stock
DB --> API: Order created

API -> Payment: Create payment
Payment --> API: Payment link
API --> Frontend: Order + Payment
Frontend --> Customer: Order confirmation

== 3. Admin Manages Order ==
Admin -> Frontend: View Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders
API -> DB: Fetch orders
DB --> API: Orders list

Admin -> Frontend: Assign to Tailor
Frontend -> API: POST /api/orders/:id/assign-tailor
API -> DB: Update order\n(assignedTailor)
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notification
DB --> Tailor: Notification

== 4. Tailor Works on Order ==
Tailor -> Frontend: View Assigned Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders/assigned
API -> DB: Fetch assigned orders
DB --> API: Orders

Tailor -> Frontend: Accept & Start Work
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/accept
API -> DB: Update status\n(status = "Cutting")
DB --> API: Order updated

Tailor -> Frontend: Update Stage
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/next-stage
API -> DB: Update status\n(status = "Stitching")
DB --> API: Order updated

Tailor -> Frontend: Mark Ready
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/mark-ready
API -> DB: Update status\n(status = "Ready")
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notifications
DB --> Customer: "Order ready"
DB --> Admin: "Order ready"

== 5. Payment Processing ==
Customer -> Frontend: View Bills
Frontend -> API: GET /api/bills
API -> DB: Fetch bills
DB --> API: Bills

Customer -> Payment: Make Payment
Payment -> API: Payment webhook
API -> DB: Update bill\n(status = "Paid")
DB --> API: Bill updated

== 6. Customer Collects Order ==
Customer -> Frontend: View Ready Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders?status=Ready
API -> DB: Fetch orders
DB --> API: Ready orders

Admin -> Frontend: Mark Delivered
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id\n(status = "Delivered")
API -> DB: Update order
DB --> API: Order updated

note over Customer,DB
  Complete Order Lifecycle:
  1. Registration
  2. Order Placement
  3. Order Assignment
  4. Order Processing
  5. Payment
  6. Delivery
end note

@enduml


